    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix F1 DU Configuration Update handling for empty operations\n\n### Summary\nThe `rrc_gNB_process_f1_du_configuration_update` function in the gNB RRC module exhibited unexpected behavior when processing F1 DU Configuration Update messages with no cell operations (add/modify/delete). Instead of properly acknowledging these no-op updates, the function would continue execution and potentially send duplicate acknowledgments or fail to respond entirely.\n\nAdditionally, when unsupported operations like cell addition or deletion were requested, the function would log warnings but still attempt to process the message as if it contained cell modifications, leading to inconsistent state handling.\n\nThe root cause was missing early-return logic for empty operation sets and improper handling of unsupported operation types. This fix ensures that:\n\n1. Empty configuration updates are immediately acknowledged with appropriate logging\n2. Unsupported operations (cells_to_add/cells_to_delete) trigger immediate acknowledgment and return\n3. Cell modification failures (ID mismatch, PLMN mismatch) properly send acknowledgment before returning\n4. All error paths consistently send a response to the DU\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/RRC/NR/rrc_gNB_du.c`: Added early return handling for empty operation sets\n- `openair2/RRC/NR/rrc_gNB_du.c`: Improved error handling for unsupported operations\n- `openair2/RRC/NR/rrc_gNB_du.c`: Fixed inconsistent acknowledgment behavior in error paths\n- `openair2/RRC/NR/rrc_gNB_du.c`: Added more descriptive logging for debugging\n\n"
}